    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Cal Raleigh** stands as our premier offensive anchor with a standout efficiency score of 79.31. Despite the southpaw matchup against Connor Prielipp, **Cal Raleigh** benefits from a high-leverage lineup slot at #2 and favorable park dynamics, making him an elite start to chase HR and RBI production. **Will Smith** follows closely at 74.95; while we are waiting on official lineup confirmation, his projected #3 spot combined with a generous 4.64 xERA matchup against Chris Paddack and wind-aided hitting conditions positions him as a high-floor play. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a core piece at 66.33, maintaining high value despite the disadvantage of facing Steven Matz because his pure power-speed profile effectively neutralizes most platoon concerns.\n\nThe bottom of our lineup reflects a cautious approach to marginal matchups. We are starting **Daulton Varsho** (48.77) and **Gavin Sheets** (43.54) primarily out of necessity; **Daulton Varsho** carries risk against the left-handed Ranger Suarez, but his position in the #2 hole provides just enough volume to justify the start. Meanwhile, **Jonathan Aranda** (43.65) and **Masyn Winn** (40.42) are hovering near our benching threshold. **Masyn Winn** is particularly concerning today due to a -5% wind-in factor and a tough matchup against Mason Montgomery. Given the off-days for **Lawrence Butler**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Bryson Stott**, and **Tyler Freeman**, our bench is currently devoid of viable alternatives to challenge these starters. We are prioritizing game cap preservation where possible, but with nearly all depth pieces inactive today, **Masyn Winn** represents the highest volatility in our active lineup; if his official order drops below #6, he is a candidate to be benched to protect our remaining games.",
